      <reaction compartment="compartment_70101" fast="false" id="reaction_8864036" metaid="metaid_86" name="PTPN12 dephosphorylates PDGFRB at Y1021" reversible="false">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Protein tyrosine phosphatase PTNP12 dephosphorylates activated PDFRB (PDGF receptor beta) at tyrosine residue Y1021, which contributes to the tumor suppressor role of PTPN12 in triple negative breast cancer in addition to PTPN12-mediated dephosphorylation of ERBB2 (HER2) at Y1248 (Sun et al. 2011).</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
          <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:vCard="http://www.w3.org/2001/vcard-rdf/3.0#" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:bqbiol="http://biomodels.net/biology-qualifiers/">
