      <reaction compartment="compartment_876" fast="false" id="reaction_9674093" metaid="metaid_90" name="PDGFRs bind type I TKI" reversible="false">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Wild-type PDGFRA and PDGFRB can be bound and inhibited by class I tyrosine kinase inhibitors including pazopanib, avapritinib, and crenolanib (Gril et al, 2013; Wang et al, 2014; Mathias et al, 2015; Meliau et al, 2017; reviewed in Klug et al, 2018). Type I inhibitors bind in the ATP binding site of the active conformation and prevent full activation of the kinase (reviewed in Roskoski, 2018).</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
          <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:vCard="http://www.w3.org/2001/vcard-rdf/3.0#" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:bqbiol="http://biomodels.net/biology-qualifiers/">
