      <reaction compartment="compartment_70101" fast="false" id="reaction_186798" metaid="metaid_94" name="GAP binds to PDGF-beta receptors only" reversible="false">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">GTPase-activating protein (GAP) has two SH2 domains which bind only to PDGF beta-receptors on Tyr771. GAP does not bind the alpha-receptor. GAP converts Ras-GTP to Ras-GDP, deactivating Ras.</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
          <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:vCard="http://www.w3.org/2001/vcard-rdf/3.0#" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:bqbiol="http://biomodels.net/biology-qualifiers/">
