      <reaction compartment="compartment_70101" fast="false" id="reaction_382052" metaid="metaid_96" name="p130Cas and C3G bind PDGFR bound Crk" reversible="false">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">The presence of both SH2 and SH3 domains in Crk proteins is of crucial importance for their function as adaptor molecules. Crk forms complex with Cas, an SH3 domain-containing docking protein which has been shown to be phosphorylated after PDGF-stimulation of cells, and C3G, a nucleotide exchange protein which has been linked to the activation of JNK.</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
