      <reaction compartment="compartment_876" fast="false" id="reaction_186819" metaid="metaid_99" name="SH2 domain of Src binds to the active receptor" reversible="false">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">The Src family of tyrosine kinases are characterized by a SH3 and a SH2 domain in addition to the kinase domain.Src is activated when the SH2 domain binds to autophosphorylation sites on PDGF receptors (Tyr579 and 581 in the beta-receptor, Tyr572 and 574 in the alpha receptor), in conjuction with dephosporylation of the COOH-terminal phosphorylated tyrosine 527.</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
          <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:vCard="http://www.w3.org/2001/vcard-rdf/3.0#" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:bqbiol="http://biomodels.net/biology-qualifiers/">
