      <reaction compartment="compartment_70101" fast="false" id="reaction_380782" metaid="metaid_105" name="STAT binds to the active receptor" reversible="false">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Among the seven members of the STAT family, STAT1, STAT3, STAT5 alpha and -beta, and STAT6 have been shown to bind to the activated PDGF beta-receptor (PDGFRB) and to be phosphorylated after PDGF stimulation; binding also occurs to the alpha-receptor (PDGFRA), albeit only weakly.</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
          <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:vCard="http://www.w3.org/2001/vcard-rdf/3.0#" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:bqbiol="http://biomodels.net/biology-qualifiers/">
