      <reaction compartment="compartment_876" fast="false" id="reaction_1524182" metaid="metaid_107" name="Activated PLC gamma dissociates from the PDGF receptor" reversible="false">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Once phosphorylated, PLCgamma dissociates from the receptor. The active enzyme promotes intracelllular signaling by catalysing the hydrolysis of PIP2 to generate the second messengers IP3 and DAG.</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
          <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:vCard="http://www.w3.org/2001/vcard-rdf/3.0#" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:bqbiol="http://biomodels.net/biology-qualifiers/">
