      <reaction compartment="compartment_70101" fast="false" id="reaction_186800" metaid="metaid_109" name="PI3K catalyses the phosphorylation of PIP2 to PIP3" reversible="false">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">The preferred substrate of PI3K is phosphatidylinositol 4,5-bisphosphate [PI(4,5)P2] (PIP2), which is phosphorylated to the trisphosphate [PI(3,4,5)P3] (PIP3). PI3-kinase and its products have been found to be of importance in PDGF-stimulated actin reorganization, and directed cell movement, as well as in the stimulation of cell growth and inhibition of apoptosis.</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
          <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:vCard="http://www.w3.org/2001/vcard-rdf/3.0#" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:bqbiol="http://biomodels.net/biology-qualifiers/">
