      <reaction compartment="compartment_876" fast="false" id="reaction_9674015" metaid="metaid_110" name="Olaratumab binds PDGFRA" reversible="false">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Olaratumab is an anti-PDGFRA specific monoclonal antibody that blocks the binding of PDGF-AA, PDGF-BB and PDGF-CC (Loizos et al, 2005). Olaratumab inhibits proliferation of a number of tumor cell lines and is approved for treatment of soft tissue sarcoma (Gerber et al, 2012; Loizos et al, 2005; Matei et al, 2006; Russell et al, 2010; Stock et al, 2007).</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
          <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:vCard="http://www.w3.org/2001/vcard-rdf/3.0#" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:bqbiol="http://biomodels.net/biology-qualifiers/">
