      <reaction compartment="compartment_70101" fast="false" id="reaction_382058" metaid="metaid_111" name="Nck binds to the active PDGF receptor" reversible="false">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Nck is a widely expressed protein consisting exclusively of SH2 and SH3 domains. With its SH2 doamin Nck interacts with Tyr571 of the PDGF beta-receptor and it also interacts with the alpha-receptor, but the sites of interaction have not been determined. Nck is involved in the activation of the JNK serine/threonine kinase through interaction with the serine/threonine kinases PAK1 and NIK.</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
          <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:vCard="http://www.w3.org/2001/vcard-rdf/3.0#" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:bqbiol="http://biomodels.net/biology-qualifiers/">
