      <reaction compartment="compartment_876" fast="false" id="reaction_186765" metaid="metaid_113" name="PLC-gamma binds to the active receptor" reversible="false">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">PLC-gamma 1 has been shown to bind to phosphorylated Tyr 1021 of the PDGF beta-receptor with high affinity and to Tyr 1009 with low affinity. In the alpha-receptor, Tyr 988 and Tyr 1018 bind PLC-gamma1. Association of PLC-gamma1 with the activated PDGF receptor has been shown to be necessary for its activation.</p>
        </notes>
